<ul>
<li>A service continuity plan is a proactive plan of action an organization will take if a service disruption occurs.</li>
<li>Plans should be developed at the time of service development and implementation.</li>
<li>Plans should also be adjusted on an ongoing basis as new risks are encountered and the operational environment changes.</li>
<li>Service continuity plans may require one or more sub plans such as a recovery or restoration plan.</li>
</ul>
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 47, 22, NULL, NULL, 602, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are service continuity plans developed and periodically reviewed  for assets required for delivery of the critical service?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
