INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (791, N'CRE.OP.2', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if security hardening guides are used to manage system configurations.

Security hardening guides (also referred to as a security configuration checklist, lockdown guide, security guide, security technical implementation guide [STIG], or benchmark) are documents that:
<ul>
<li>Include instructions or procedures for configuring an IT product to an operational environment.</li>
<li>Verify that the product has been configured properly.</li>
<li>And/or help identify unauthorized configuration changes to the product.</li>
</ul>

The IT product may be commercial, open source, government-off-the-shelf (GOTS), etc.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 23, NULL, NULL, 711, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Does the organization manage system configurations using security hardening guides?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>Security hardening guides (or security configuration checklists, lockdown guides, security guides, security technical implementation guides [STIGs], or benchmarks) are used to manage the organization’s system configurations.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (792, N'CRE.OP.3', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if the organization has identified and removed all unsupported hardware and software from its operating environment.

Remove unsupported hardware and software. Supported hardware and software generally allow you to receive updates and patches for vulnerabilities that otherwise are not available for unsupported assets.

If hardware or software is unsupported, yet necessary for the fulfillment of the enterprise’s mission, document an exception detailing mitigating controls and residual risk acceptance. For any unsupported hardware or software without an exception documentation, designate as unauthorized. Review the hardware and software list to periodically verify support.

Operational environments may present unique requirements. The security challenges facing Industrial Control Systems (ICS) will require additional attention and consideration. For example, many utilize proprietary protocols and may not have the ability to support security software that is commonly used in a traditional Information Technology (IT) environment.

ICS network architectures typically differ from traditional IT environments and may require the organization to employ compensating controls. Applying security controls to ICS often rely on segmentation and boundary control between the IT and OT domains, and careful control design around local and remote connectivity to reduce attack vectors used to gain access to ICS networks.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 23, NULL, NULL, 712, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Has the organization removed all unsupported hardware and software to apply the security best practices.', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization identifies and, where appropriate, removes all unsupported hardware and software from its operating environment.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (793, N'CRE.OP.4', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if services are identified.
<ul>
<li>A service is a set of activities that the organization carries out in the performance of a duty or in the production of a product.</li>
<li>Services can be externally or internally focused. Examples can include: (1) a customer-facing website such as an online payment system, (2) human resources transactions</li>
<li>A fundamental operational resilience objective is to focus on activities to protect and sustain the identified services and assets that most directly affect the organization''s ability to achieve its mission.</li>
</ul>
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 23, NULL, NULL, 713, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are services identified?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
