INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (871, N'CRE.OP.82', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if the organization has defined risk criteria and if risk tolerances thresholds have been defined for each criteria.
<ul>
<li>Organizational risk assessments are used, in part, to inform the security and privacy control selection process. The selection process results in an agreed-upon set of security and privacy controls addressing specific mission or business needs consistent with organizational risk tolerance.</li>
<li>Risk framing is most effective when conducted at the organization level and in consultation with stakeholders throughout the organization including mission, business, and system owners. The assumptions, constraints, risk tolerance, priorities, and trade-offs identified as part of the risk framing process inform the risk management strategy, which in turn informs the conduct of risk assessment, risk response, and risk monitoring activities.</li>
<li>Risk tolerance is defined as the level of risk or the degree of uncertainty that is acceptable to an organization.</li>
<li>Risk parameters may differ for each impact area. Risk tolerance parameters describe the risk measurement criteria for each impact area. Risk measurement criteria include how impact is measured, how frequently it is measured, and what is to be measured.</li>
</ul>
.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 81, 23, NULL, NULL, 736, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Has the organization defined organizational risk criteria and tolerances?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization has defined risk criteria and risk tolerance thresholds for each criteria of risk.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (872, N'CRE.OP.83', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine whether the organization considers risk inheritance and exposure between its various interconnected systems.

Organizations should consider the risk related to new or increased threats that may be introduced when systems exchange information with other systems that may have different security and privacy requirements and controls. This includes systems within the same organization and systems that are external to the organization.

Risk assessments can support a wide variety of risk-based decisions and activities including the definition of interconnection security requirements for information exchange. System information exchange security requirements apply to information exchanges between two or more systems. Examples include:
<ul>
<li>System information exchanges include connections via leased lines</li>
<li>Virtual private networks</li>
<li>Connections to internet service providers</li>
<li>Connections and exchanges with cloud services</li>
<li>Exchanges via web-based services</li>
<li>Exchanges of files via file transfer protocol</li>
<li>Other organization-to-organization communications.</li>
</ul>
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 82, 23, NULL, NULL, 736, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Does the organization consider risk inheritance and exposure between its various interconnected systems?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization considers risk inheritance and exposure between all of its interconnected systems.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (873, N'CRE.OP.84', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if the organization performs business impact assessments as part of its service continuity program.

The Business Impact Analysis (BIA) is a foundational element of a service continuity program. The BIA measures the effects of a disruption on an organization’s services and how they impact changes over time.

Leverage business impact assessments to prioritize resources and identify which systems must be recovered first. Business impact analysis helps identify and prioritize critical systems, information, and assets. This information determines contingency requirements and priorities for critical information and services. It also allows planning for disruption impacts and identifies allowable outage times. This enables personnel to develop and prioritize recovery strategies that can be used.

Possible Actions:
<ul>
<li>Define business impact analysis characteristics.</li>
<li>Establish a link to risk assessments</li>
<li>Determine how to measure the impact of a service disruption.</li>
</ul>
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 83, 23, NULL, NULL, 736, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Does the organization perform business impact assessments?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization performs business impact assessments to identify critical business services and assets.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (874, N'CRE.OP.85', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if sources of risk that can affect operations have been identified.
 •     Operational risk is defined as the potential impact on assets and the related services --the risk that results from operating services and assets on a day-to-day basis.
 •     Operational risk sources are the fundamental areas of risk that can affect the critical service and associated assets.
 •     Identifying risk sources or areas of risk helps the organization determine and categorize the types of operational risk that are most likely to affect day-to-day operations.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 84, 23, NULL, NULL, 737, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Have sources of risk that can affect operations been identified?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     Sources of risk that can affect operation of the critical service have been identified and documented.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     Sources of risk that can affect operation of the critical service are being identified and are partially documented.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (875, N'CRE.OP.86', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if categories have been established for risks.
 •     Risk categories provide a means for collecting and organizing risk for ease of analysis and mitigation.
 •     Operational risk categories typically align with the sources of operational risk.
 •     Risk categories can be as granular as necessary for the organization to effectively manage risk.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 85, 23, NULL, NULL, 737, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Have categories been established for risks?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     Categories of risk that can affect the critical service have been established and documented.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     Categories of risk that can affect the critical service are being established and are partially documented.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (876, N'CRE.OP.87', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if a plan for managing operational risk has been established.
 •     The plan provides a common foundation for the performance of operational risk management activities.
 •     The operational risk management plan should be developed to facilitate the accumulation of operational risks as input to the organization''s enterprise risk management program.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 86, 23, NULL, NULL, 737, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Has a plan for managing operational risk been established?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     There is a documented plan for managing operational risk.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     A plan is in development and partially documented.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (877, N'CRE.OP.88', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if the plan for managing operational risk is communicated to stakeholders.
 •     Relevant stakeholders can be internal or external to the organization and are responsible for operational risk management activities.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 87, 23, NULL, NULL, 737, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Is the plan for managing operational risk communicated to stakeholders?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     The plan for managing operational risk is communicated to all stakeholders that support the critical service.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     The plan for managing operational risk is communicated to some stakeholders.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (878, N'CRE.OP.89', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if risk tolerance thresholds, which trigger action, are defined for each category of risk.
 •     Risk tolerance parameters describe the risk measurement criteria for each impact area.
 •     Risk tolerance thresholds are used by management to determine when a risk is in control or when it has exceeded acceptable limits.

Risk tolerance thresholds should be set for each category of risk that the organization establishes as a means for measuring and managing risk. For example:
 •     A risk tolerance threshold for a category of risk may be whenever more than 200 users are impacted.
 •     The risk tolerance threshold indicates when action needs to be taken to prevent operational disruption.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 88, 23, NULL, NULL, 738, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are risk tolerance thresholds, which trigger action, defined for each category of risk?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     The organization has established a risk tolerance threshold for each category of risk defined for the critical service.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     The organization has established a risk tolerance threshold for some categories of risk defined for the critical service.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (879, N'CRE.OP.90', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if plans are developed for risks that the organization decides to mitigate.
 •     Risk mitigation plans should be developed when operational risk exceeds the organization''s risk threshold and are determined to be unacceptable.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 89, 23, NULL, NULL, 739, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are plans developed for risks that the organization decides to mitigate?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     Risk mitigation plans are developed and documented for all risks that the organization decides to mitigate.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     Risk mitigation plans are in development and partially documented.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (880, N'CRE.OP.91', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if identified risks are tracked to closure.
 •     The disposition of risks must be tracked, periodically assessed, and revised as necessary.
 •     The organization should provide a method for tracking open risks to closure.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 90, 23, NULL, NULL, 739, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are identified risks tracked to closure?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     All identified risks are tracked to closure.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     Some identified risks are tracked to closure.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (881, N'CRE.OP.92', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if staff members are assigned to execute specific service continuity plans.
<ul>
<li>The activities documented in the service continuity plan must be assigned to responsible and skilled individuals in the event that the plan must be executed.</li>
<li>These staff members may be internal or external (through outsourcing arrangements and service contracts) to the organization.</li>
</ul>
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 91, 23, NULL, NULL, 740, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are staff members assigned to execute specific service continuity plans?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization has assigned staff required for the execution of each service continuity plan established for the critical service.</li>
</ul>

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization has assigned staff required for the execution of some plans.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (882, N'CRE.OP.93', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if key contacts are identified in service continuity plans.
<ul>
<li>The critical service may depend on assets both internal and external to the organization.</li>
<li>Services may also rely on external partnerships such as public agencies and infrastructure providers (public utilities, telecommunications, etc.).</li>
<li>Key contacts can therefore be internal or external to the organization.</li>
</ul>
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 92, 23, NULL, NULL, 740, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are key contacts identified in the service continuity plans?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization has identified key contacts in each service continuity plan established for the critical service.</li>
</ul>

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization has identified key contacts in some of the service continuity plans.</li>
<li>Or; The organization has identified some key contacts in the service continuity plans.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (883, N'CRE.OP.94', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if service continuity plans are stored in a controlled manner and available to those who need to know.
<ul>
<li>The ability to execute service continuity plans during a disruption depends on their accessibility and integrity.</li>
</ul>

The organization must take steps to ensure that the plans are:
<ul>
<li>Archived in a controlled manner up to date and available.</li>
<li>Secured and free from unapproved modification readily retrievable, when necessary, by those who need access to them.</li>
</ul>
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 93, 23, NULL, NULL, 740, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are service continuity plans stored in a controlled manner and available to all those who need to know?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization stores all service continuity plans for the critical service in a controlled manner, and the plans are available to all who need to know.</li>
</ul>

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization stores all service continuity plans for the critical service in a controlled manner, and the plans are available to some who need to know.</li>
<li>Or; the organization stores some service continuity plans for the critical service in a controlled manner, and those plans are available to all who need to know.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (884, N'CRE.OP.95', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if mechanisms are implemented to achieve resilience requirements in normal and adverse situations. The organization must plan to sustain technology assets to ensure the continued operation of services.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 94, 23, NULL, NULL, 740, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are mechanisms (e.g., failsafe, load balancing, hot swap capabilities) implemented to achieve resilience requirements in normal and adverse situations?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>Mechanisms are implemented to achieve resilience requirements for normal and adverse situations, where appropriate, for all assets that support the critical service.</li>
</ul>

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
<ul>
<li>Mechanisms are implemented to achieve resilience requirements for normal and adverse situations, where appropriate, for some assets.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (885, N'CRE.OP.96', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if plans are reviewed to identify and resolve conflicts.
<ul>
<li>Service continuity plans often overlap and rely on the same set of organizational resources. For example:</li>
<li>An offsite facility that is named in more than one plan may not be able to satisfy requirements if multiple plans are executed simultaneously.</li>
<li>Multiple service continuity plans, which may need to be executed simultaneously, often rely on the same people.</li>
</ul>
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 95, 23, NULL, NULL, 740, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are plans reviewed to identify and resolve conflicts?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization reviews all service continuity plans that support the critical service to identify and resolve conflicts.</li>
</ul>

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
<ul>
<li>The organization reviews some service continuity plans to identify and resolve conflicts.</li>
</ul>
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (886, N'CRE.OP.97', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if test results are compared to test objectives to identify improvements to service continuity plans.
 •     The objective of service continuity plan testing is to ensure that plans work as intended.
 •     Testing identifies required improvements to the service continuity plans as well as the associated test plans.

The evaluation of test results involves comparing the documented test results against the established test objectives:
 •     Areas where objectives could not be met are recorded, and strategies are developed to review and revise the plans.
 •     Improvements to the testing process and plans should also be identified, documented, and incorporated into future tests.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 96, 23, NULL, NULL, 740, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Service with test objectives to identify needed improvements to service continuity plans?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     Test results for each service continuity plan required for the delivery of the critical service are compared with test objectives to identify needed improvements.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     Test results for some service continuity plans are compared with test objectives to identify needed improvements.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (887, N'CRE.OP.98', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if conditions have been identified that trigger the execution of the service continuity plan.
 •     The organization must be able to determine when the plan must be executed and who is responsible for initiating action.
 •     The organization should ensure that owners of service continuity plans understand the conditions for execution.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 97, 23, NULL, NULL, 740, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Have conditions been identified that trigger the execution of the service continuity plan?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     Conditions that trigger the execution of each service continuity plan that supports the critical service have been identified and documented.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     Conditions that trigger the execution of some service continuity plans have been identified and documented.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (888, N'CRE.OP.99', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if improvements are identified as a result of executing service continuity plans.
 •     As a result of the review of executed service continuity plans, improvements are identified and documented.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 98, 23, NULL, NULL, 740, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Are improvements identified as a result of executing service continuity plans?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
 •     Improvements to each executed service continuity plan that supports the critical service are identified and documented.
 •     Or; if service continuity plans have not been executed, the identification of improvements to executed plans is required as part of a standard process.

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
 •     Improvements to some executed service continuity plans are identified and documented.
')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[MATURITY_QUESTIONS] ([Mat_Question_Id], [Question_Title], [Question_Text], [Supplemental_Info], [Category], [Sub_Category], [Maturity_Level_Id], [Sequence], [Maturity_Model_Id], [Parent_Question_Id], [Ranking], [Grouping_Id], [Examination_Approach], [Short_Name], [Mat_Question_Type], [Parent_Option_Id], [Supplemental_Fact], [Scope], [Recommend_Action], [Risk_Addressed], [Services], [Outcome], [Security_Practice], [Implementation_Guides]) VALUES (889, N'CRE.OP.100', N'', N'<div class="sub-header-1">Question Intent</div><div>To determine if the responsibility for monitoring sources of threat information has been assigned. Effective threat monitoring requires the assignment of responsibility for threat monitoring activities.
 •     Threat monitoring is a process of data collection and distribution with the purpose of providing timely, accurate, complete, and relevant information about the organization''s current threat environment.
 •     Threat monitoring is an integral part of establishing a common operating picture for the organization.
</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, 99, 23, NULL, NULL, 741, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Has responsibility for monitoring sources of threat information been assigned?', N'<div class="sub-header-2">Implemented</div>
<ul>
<li>The responsibility for monitoring all sources of threat information relevant to the critical service has been assigned.</li>
</ul>

<div class="sub-header-2">In Progress</div>
<ul>
<li>The responsibility for monitoring some sources of threat information has been assigned.</li>
